RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 80. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 45000. FOR FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES AND CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 24 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $50 ,000. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGHLANDS broke a step slow from outside, steered down to the rail trailing early, inched closer up the backstretch, had to pause briefly behind INTO YELLOWSTONE and altered out to the three path midway around the far turn, challenged ACCLAIMED PREACHER into the stretch, took over with a furlong left to run and drew off in deep stretch. ACCLAIMED PREACHER broke well then raced keenly under some restraint three deep into the first turn, moved into the two path chasing the leaders around the clubhouse turn, bid three deep on the second bend, cleared past the quarter pole but was soon challenged by HIGHLANDS entering the lane, dueled to the eighth pole and was no match for the winner in the furlongs grounds but stayed on to secure the place. SAKURA BLOSSOM tracked in the two path, trailed on the inside into the far turn, came two wide into the stretch, moved to with striking distance with a furlong left to run but finished evenly late. MISS PIXY STIX dueled for command from inside, fought inside rivals on the far turn, lost touch with ACCLAIMED PREACHER past the quarter pole and weakened. INTO YELLOWSTONE off slow in the beginning, rushed up between rivals then dueled outside MISS PIXY STICK, fought between on the far turn then started to weaken around the bend and retreated in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 94. Claiming Purse 30000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCIP forwardly placed early, bid three deep at the quarter pole, put away inner rivals approaching the eighth pole and was ridden out while drawing off. VAGABOND SHOES bumped by inner rival at the start, took a bump from BRACE FOR IMPACT early, went up to press the pace from outside while tugging in hand, raced on even terms around the bend, fought between rivals past the quarter pole, could not kick on with PRINCIP in the final furlong but stayed on to secure second. COOL PAPA G off a bit slow to begin, chased outside a rival early, three then four wide on the turn, got to within striking distance entering the furlong grounds but needed to find more late. SUPERMAX broke out and bumped VAGABOND SHOES and dropped back, went four wide into the turn, trailed while angling down to the two path around the bend and churned on to improve position. STORM THE NIGHT sped clear then set the pace inside a rival up the backstretch, dueled around the turn then vied inside rivals late on the bend, fought to upper stretch and weakened, pulled up and unsaddled following the race and walked off. EAGLES LANDING chased along the rail into the turn, steered out and came five wide into the lane and weakened. BRACE FOR IMPACT drifted in and bumped rival early losing his action for a couple jumps, chased four wide into the turn, six wide into the lane and came up empty.

ENTRY.NAME: Storm the Night
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, dueled inside, weakened, walked off

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped 2x early, pressed/keen, dueled outside, held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 98. Starter Allowance Purse 36000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 24 Allowed 2 lbs. (Rail at 24 fee t).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SINGLE TRACK MIND (IRE) unhurried in the beginning and moved inside, swung out with a quarter mile remaining, rallied and drew alongside MEGA MOON with a sixteenth remaining and drove past late. MEGA MOON tracked in the two path, between rivals on the far turn, chased three wide turning for home, collared entering deep stretch and took over but got outkicked by the winner. SANGER stepped to the front and moved inside, coaxed along on the far turn still clear of the field, put to right handed urging in upper stretch, remained unchallenged into the final furlong but was reeled in at the sixteenth pole by outer rivals and saved the show. ST IGNACIO tucked inside at the back, angled out on the far turn and came six wide into the lane, showed a mild response to urging but could not get by SANGER for the show. REMOTE stalked three deep early, remained off the rail and came four wide into the drive, steadied past the eighth pole and was ridden out to the wire. GOLDENEYE closest in pursuit in the two path, came under a ride on the far turn, chased the leader into the final furlong and weakened in deep stretch. DISCRETIONARY DAY stalked the pace from inside, ridden along the rail through the second bend and faded. THE RIDER ABOARD REMOTE LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST SINGLE TRACK MIND (IRE) FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH. FOLLOWING A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THE INCIDENT DID NOT WARRANT A DISQUALIFICATION AND THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED.

ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, inside, angled out 1/4, up late

BIG BUZZ bobbled leaving the gate, trailed on the inside early, moved out on the backstretch, rallied four wide on the far turn, got to within range of GIOVINAZZO in the stretch but lacked the needed late punch to threaten the winner. GOOD JUJU chased four then three wide early, moved up alongside the leaders three deep in the middle stages, lost touch with the leader approaching the quarter pole, spun three wide into the lane and weakened. SEATTLE BREAKOUT raced up close three to four wide on the first turn, pressed between rivals to the far turn, could not keep pace with GIOVINAZZO past the five-sixteenths pole and weakened in the drive. SETTECENTO tracked inside to two wide on the clubhouse turn, went three then four wide on the second bend and lacked the needed response. PARK CITY stumbled leaving the gate, tracked three wide into the first turn then angled over to the inside, saved ground through the far turn and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEER MONEY vied for the lead inside several rivals then dueled leaving the backstretch, cleared outer rival at the quarter pole, kept to task through the lane and held safely. STAGGER LEE broke a step slow, chased out of range early, saved ground then tipped two wide into the stretch, moved out further in the lane and put in a mild late bid to close the gap on the winner and gain second. DON'T HIT ME BASH showed early speed three deep between rivals then ceded command and moved inside to chase the top pair leaving the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, cornered nicely into the stretch and lacked a late bid. FACT OR FICTION sent between rivals early then dueled outside BEER MONEY leaving the backstretch, kept the pressure on early on the turn then failed to match strides with the winner approaching the quarter pole and weakened down the lane. NO SHOW JONES dropped back under coaxing on the inside, saved ground into the lane, moved out and could not make an impact. RUN BRYCE RUN broke a step slow, trailed up the backstretch and passed tired rivals. SMILING JOJO showed speed five deep early then chased three deep leaving the backstretch, rounded the bend three then four wide and faded down the lane. WHO IS PAVEL showed early speed four deep between rivals then chased between rivals up the backstretch, raced two then three wide on the turn and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 22000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONTANA chased three then two wide on the first turn, inched closer three deep in the middle stages, came under a ride on the far turn, spun three wide into the lane, chased after the leader into deep stretch and dug in late overtake the runner-up in the closing moments. CHAOS REIGNS cleared and steered to the inside, set all the pace to the stretch, put to the left hand with a furlong remaining, challenged by MONTANA late and could not hold that rival at bay. MY PARTNER GLEN went four wide into the first turn then angled in a few paths, advanced between rivals on the backstretch and far turn, tipped four wide into the lane but needed to find more to threaten the top pair. VENOM tracked four wide then three deep on the first turn, rounded the second bend in the four path and weakened down the lane. REEF CITY tracked in the two path then got bumped from inside on the first turn, saved ground through far turn and lacked a response when called upon. DONTTESTYOURLUCK sent from the gate and chased on the inside before lugging out and bumping rival while rank on the first turn, ridden along three then four deep on the backstretch, traveled in the four path turning for home and failed to menace. RANGER JOE forwardly placed on the inside early, started to weaken around the far turn and tired down the lane. LEN'S LUCK became fractious in the gate, broke a step slow, traveled along the inside and tired. BIG GEORGE antsy in the gate, broke poorly, got forced out on the first turn then moved back inward, traveled three deep into the second bend, spun three wide into the lane and came up empty.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Hollywood Turf Cup S. - Grade2 DEL MAR RACE 7 1 1/2M Turf CR: 109. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $200 each to accompany the nomination, Closed Thursday November 16,2023 with 14 or by supplementary nomination of $2,000 each by the closing time of entries. Closed with 1(Francesco Clemente) $3,000 addi tional to start, with $200,000 Guaranteed, of which $120,000 to first, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. Three-year-olds 122 lbs. Older 126 lbs. Non-winners of a Gr I at one mile or over in 2022-23 allowed 2 lbs., a Gr II at a mile or over in 2022-23, 4 lbs. This race will not be divided. High weights preferred. Second preference will be given to horses placed (second or third) in a Gr I or Gr II in 2023 or Gr III winners in 2023. Total non-claiming earnings in 20 23 will be used in determining the order of preference of horses with equal status. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PLANETARIO (BRZ) broke a step slow then tucked inside near the back, drew closer while moving off the rail to the two path on the far turn still patiently handled, split foes in upper stretch and rallied to take over midstretch and held gamely over outer rivals in the final moments. FRANCESCO CLEMENTE (IRE) was off slow to begin and trailed on the inside, continued at the back to the final bend, swung out into the stretch, rallied widest and missed. LUKKA (CHI) settled along the inside, rounded the clubhouse turn in the two path, chased three deep into the lane, bid four deep with a furlong left to run and finished gamely between late. BALLADEER sprinted clear and crossed to the inside, pressured a bit on the backstretch before moving clear past the half-mile pole, ridden along on the final bend, put to right handed urging at the top of the stretch, showed the way to the eighth pole, challenged by several rivals in the furlong grounds and weakened. SPEAKING SCOUT sat off the pace outside a rival in the two path, spun three wide into the lane, steered out in upper stretch and lacked a rally. EASTERN OCEAN angled to the inside chasing out of range, inched closer on the clubhouse turn, waited for room with a quarter mile left to run, tried to tip out in upper stretch but got hemmed in at the eighth pole, moved out into the clear midstretch but could not regain momentum. ASTRONAUT stalked from inside then moved into the two path, applied some pressure early on the backstretch before chasing again past the half-mile pole, , came under a ride midway on the final turn, took aim at the leader in the two path entering the lane, moved out in upper stretch and weakened.

YO YO MAMA bumped leaving the gate, raced in tight early then advanced between rivals, chased outside a rival into the turn, got carried wide leaving the bend and weakened. SQUARE TOMATOES bumped with YO YO MAMA at the start, traveled off the rail then between foes into the turn, rounded the bend two then three wide and lacked a rally. KEEP YOUR COIL took a bump from the winner early, trailed two wide then moved out in the lane and proved no menace. COCKTAIL PRINCESS dueled for command from outside then cleared past the half-mile pole and crossed over to the inside, challenged again into the turn, dueled around the bend and into the lane, could not kick on with the winner in upper stretch and gave way.
